article.headline: UNC Asheville 84, Liberty 77
article.story: ASHEVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Bryan Smithson scored 21 points to lead four players in double-digit scoring as UNC Asheville defeated Liberty 84-77 on Saturday. K.J. Garland added 17 points and Vincent James had 12 for the Bulldogs (5-10, 1-0), who made 21 of 25 (84 percent) form the free-throw line. Garrett Moles had a double-double with 10 points and 10 rebounds. Larry Blair scored 21 points to lead three players in double-digit scoring for Liberty (6-9, 0-1), which shot 13-for-16 (81.3 percent) from the line. Dwight Brewington added 16 points and Alex McClean finished with 15.
